# IncidentIQ - Cursor Rules

- Project: IncidentIQ RAG Application homework submission.
- Working directory: C:\dev\amdocs-ai-course\projects\incidentiq\
- Keep secrets out of git and Docker images. Use .env locally, Render secret env vars in production, and .env.example for placeholders only.
- Keep the Dockerfile in this project root and preserve Docker best practices: slim official base image, requirements copied before source, no embedded keys, EXPOSE 8000, and a CMD that starts FastAPI.
- Use pathlib.Path for file paths so the project works on Windows and Linux containers.
- Type hints are required on every function and method signature.
- Docstrings are required on classes and public methods.
- Use structured logging through app.utils.logger; do not use print() in production code.
- Catch specific exceptions; do not use bare except.
- Keep RAG answers grounded in retrieved FAISS context and handle empty or irrelevant queries explicitly.
- FAISS index path: knowledge_base/faiss_index/
- Embedding model: all-MiniLM-L6-v2
- LLM: OpenAI gpt-4o-mini primary; Gemini gemini-2.0-flash fallback when configured.
- Document ingestion: TXT, PDF, DOCX, XLSX from data/documents/
- Tests must run with pytest using pytest.ini.
- Stack: FastAPI + FAISS + sentence-transformers + OpenAI + Gemini + Docker + Render.
